.SS model-health
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl model-health [arguments]\f[R]
M060 D-09 (R10102-R10105): unified hardware-pressure core \[em] Linux
PSI (/proc/pressure cpu/mem/io) + dual-CCD topology (M070) + GPU
(nvidia-smi) + ZFS pool/dataset latency (M068) + scheduler backpressure
(M058).
Read -only; the sovereign-hardware-pressure-api daemon serves the D-09
cockpit dashboard from this same core.
Verbs: status / psi / zfs (+ \[en]json).
.PP
Run \f[V]sovereign-osctl help\f[R] for the complete version-matched
grammar.
.SS costs
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl costs [arguments]\f[R]
M060 D-05 (R10083-R10087): M049 13-field span store + query core \[em]
reads the observability fabric\[cq]s append-only span log
(/var/log/sovereign-os/spans.jsonl), filters by time window / text /
severity / OCSF class (MS026 16-event taxonomy), assembles per-trace
span trees.
Read-only; the sovereign-traces-api daemon serves the D-05 cockpit
dashboard from this same core.
Verbs: spans / trace / summary (+ \[en]json, \[en]window, \[en]q,
\[en]severity, \[en]ocsf-class).
.PP
Run \f[V]sovereign-osctl help\f[R] for the complete version-matched
grammar.
.SS cost-policy
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl cost-policy [arguments]\f[R]
M060 D-04 (R10075-R10082): cost aggregation core \[em] joins the
operator cost policy (/etc/sovereign-os/cost-policy.toml, dump
9885-9930) to the per-span cost attribute of the M049 span log,
aggregating daily / project / MS040-profile / model spend + 30-day trend
+ end-of-day forecast.
Read-only; the sovereign-costs-api daemon serves the D-04 cockpit
dashboard from this same core.
Verbs: summary / policy / today / export {csv|json} (+ \[en]json).
Read-only \[em] the WRITE side is cost-policy.
.PP
Run \f[V]sovereign-osctl help\f[R] for the complete version-matched
grammar.
.SS adapters
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl adapters [arguments]\f[R]
M060 D-04 write surface \[em] flip cloud_enabled in
/etc/sovereign-os/cost-policy.toml so the operator can HALT (or resume)
all cloud spend from the cockpit.
DRY-RUN by default; a real write needs \[en]confirm (baked into the
control-systems change_cli) AND, via the exec daemon, the operator key +
type-to-confirm + SOVEREIGN_OS_ACTION_EXEC_LIVE.
Verbs: show / halt-cloud / resume-cloud.
.PP
Run \f[V]sovereign-osctl help\f[R] for the complete version-matched
grammar.
.SS evals
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl evals [arguments]\f[R]
SDD-061 (M046): the GATE-PRODUCER \[em] advance an adapter\[cq]s MS041
gate from REAL evidence.
adapters gate {human|snapshot|eval|oracle} → adapter-gate.py: human =
operator attestation (the sole cockpit control, adapter-gate-human);
snapshot = a real ZFS rollback-point (SDD-050); eval = a real passing
evals.jsonl record (D-10); oracle = an oracle-backend judge.
SB-077: honest-defer (gate stays pending) when the evidence/backend is
absent \[em] never fabricates a pass.
eval/snapshot/oracle are CLI-\&...
.PP
Run \f[V]sovereign-osctl help\f[R] for the complete version-matched
grammar.
.SS super-model
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl super-model [arguments]\f[R]
M060 chain health observability \[em] proxies the selfdef daemon\[cq]s
GET /v1/m060/health endpoint reporting publish-freshness of all 10
mirror artifacts (offline/degraded/stale/online plus this script\[cq]s
own \[lq]unreachable\[rq] when the daemon is down).
Used by the D-00 master-dashboard\[cq]s chain-health banner, the MCP
tool selfdef-m060-health, and ops/smoke scripts.
Read-only.
Verbs: probe / state (+ \[en]json).
.PP
Run \f[V]sovereign-osctl help\f[R] for the complete version-matched
grammar.
